Upstream-Name: libvgm
Upstream-Contact: ValleyBell <https://github.com/ValleyBell/libvgm/issues>
Source: https://github.com/ValleyBell/libvgm
Comment: Upstream does not ship a top-level LICENSE or COPYING file. The
 codebase is a modular rewrite of audio components from VGMPlay (GPL-2.0+)
 and incorporates sound-chip emulator cores from MAME, Nuked-OPM/OPL/OPLL,
 and other emulator projects that carry their own per-file license headers.
 The licenses observed in the source tree are GPL-2.0+, GPL-2.0, LGPL-2.1+,
 BSD-3-Clause, and MIT (build-system helpers). As the combined work is
 linked together, the resulting binaries and shared libraries are GPL-2.0+
 in effect — that is the umbrella license declared below. Individual files
 retain their own license terms; the more permissive per-file licenses
 (LGPL-2.1+, BSD-3-Clause, MIT) apply when those files are reused outside
 the combined libvgm work. Notable per-file licenses observed:
 .
   * emu/cores/nukedopm.c, nukedopl3_int.h, ym3438_int.h    LGPL-2.1+
   * emu/cores/c352.c, msm5205.c, okiadpcm.h                BSD-3-Clause
   * emu/cores/fmopn.c, nes_defs.h, ym2413.c, ymf262.c,
     nukedopll_int.h, pwm.c, vsu.c, adlibemu_opl_inc.c,
     Ootake_PSG_private.h, ym3438.c, nukedopll.c            GPL-2.0+ or GPL-2.0
   * cmake/sanitizers/* (build-helpers, not shipped)        MIT
   * cmake/joinpaths/JoinPaths.cmake (build-helper, not
     shipped)                                                MIT or CC0-1.0

